          WWWOFFLE - World Wide Web Offline Explorer - Version 2.8f
          =========================================================

These are miscellaneous files/scripts that can be used with WWWOFFLE.

Contents:

        WWWOFFLE basic scripts
        Ht://Dig basic scripts
        Dialup scripts


WWWOFFLE
--------

Contributed: Andrew M. Bishop <amb@gedanken.demon.co.uk> [WWWOFFLE Author]

start.bat       Starts WWWOFFLE.
stop.bat        Stops WWWOFFLE.
online.bat      Puts WWWOFFLE online and starts fetching.
offline.bat     Puts WWWOFFLE online.


ht://Dig
--------

Contributed: Andrew M. Bishop <amb@gedanken.demon.co.uk> [WWWOFFLE Author]

dig-full.bat    Does a full htdig.
dig-incr.bat    Does an incremental htdig.
dig-last.bat    Does an htdig of the lasttime directory.
fuzzy.bat       Creates the fuzzy database for htdig.


Dialup
------

Contributed: Jan Tisje <jan.tisje@gmx.de>

dialup-scripts/dialup_vars.sh
dialup-scripts/offline.sh
dialup-scripts/online.sh

These scripts can be configured to be run by WWWOFFLE when it goes online or
offline so that Windows dial up networking is started and stopped.
